    article_id: "f46dbf16f30d5b5ada5414958c153f39",
    title:
      "Abbie Chatfield Sheds Light on Striking Wage Disparity with Male Peers",
    link: "https://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-12512673/Abbie-Chatfield-earned-money-male-colleagues.html?ns_mchannel=rss&ns_campaign=1490&ito=1490",
    keywords: "null",
    creator: "null",
    description:
      "Abbie Chatfield has opened up about her experiences with pay disparity during her pre-TV career.",
    content:
      "\n<p>Abbie Chatfield has recently publicly discussed the severe wage inequality she experienced prior to embarking on her television career. Known for her hosting role on The Masked Singer Australia and appearance in The Bachelor, Chatfield was once a commercial real estate analyst. It was during this time she first encountered wage disparity. </p>\n\n<h2> Initial Exposure to Pay Gap </h2>\n<p>Chatfield shared intimate details about her early career experiences on tech mogul Meggie Palmer`s podcast, It’s A Lot. Palmer, a leading figure in the tech industry and the founder and CEO of PepTalkHer, welcomed a frank conversation in which Chatfield divulged she was grossly underpaid compared to her male peers.</p>\n\n<p>With a degree in property economics, Chatfield entered the workforce with a clear understanding of her worth. However, after consulting her male colleagues about their salaries, she was surprised to discover they were earning at least $20,000 more than her.</p>\n\n<h2> A Double Burden </h2>\n<p>Moreover, Chatfield pointed out that she was not just performing her designated analyst tasks--she was also bearing extra administrative responsibilities for the company. Observing that this is a common pattern amongst women who often have to accept ”foot in the door” jobs, Chatfield stated that these women are often overloaded with extra duties while being paid less.</p>\n\n<p>Despite acknowledging these dual responsibilities during a performance review and highlighting her contributions to cost-saving efforts of the company, Chatfield was initially informed that a salary raise was not possible due to budget constraints. However, after confronting her superiors with her revelation about her peers` pay disparity, she was granted a salary increase of $20,000.</p>\n\n<h2> A New Chapter Begins </h2>\n<p>Reflecting on her past endeavors, Chatfield coined the situation as ”f**ked.” This led her to switch careers, venturing onto The Bachelor, which marked a turning point in her media career. As she navigated her increasing responsibilities, Chatfield recently announced she is seeking a personal assistant to share her workload.</p>\n\n<p>Chatfield, who has been feeling the pressure of her booming media career, took to Instagram to re-advertise the role, hoping to ensure maximum visibility. She received several exceptional candidates and plans to conduct interviews over the coming weekend.</p>\n\n<h2> Seeking a Proactive Assistant </h2>\n<p>The role Chatfield is seeking to fill is not meant for the faint of heart. She seeks an individual who excels at foreseeing problems and streamlining her life before issues present themselves. Her ideal candidate needs to handle her life admin tasks, care for her dog Mr.Walter when she`s working, and keep her on track.</p>\n\n<p>The individual should have proficient organizational skills and the ability to identify problems before they materialize and provide effective solutions. Her job post concluded with, ”ADHD girly needs guidance basically.”</p>\n\n<h2> Perks of the Role </h2>\n<p>As an additional perk, Chatfield promises the successful applicant a behind-the-scenes insight into TV and podcasting, indisputably valuable experiences in the entertainment industry. However, she clearly has a preference for candidates with personal assistant or TV runner experience.</p>\n\n<p>No explicit mention of salary or benefits has been shared yet, but the eventual assistant will need to be comfortable with traveling around Sydney as per Abbie`s requirements. There’s no denying Chatfield’s open discussion of past wage discrimination will continue to fuel conversations about wage disparity between different genders. </p>",
