    description:
      "Follow Mail Sport`s live blog for all the latest news and updates from Old Trafford on Wednesday.",
    content:
      "\n<p>Authored by James Cohen for Mailonline - Published: 04:03 EDT, 13 September 2023 | Updated: 08:19 EDT, 13 September 2023 </p>\n\n<p>Catch the latest updates and news about Manchester United throughout the day in our live blog from Old Trafford. </p>\n\n<h2>12:20 The Transformation of Paul Pogba: From a Sensational £89m Deal with Man United and World Cup Victory to Injuries and Alleged Extortions</h2>\n\n<p>Monday was distinctly chaotic even by Paul Pogba`s standards. The morning started with news of Pogba contemplating quitting football after an alleged extortion scheme involving his sibling. By evening, news emerged that he was staring down the barrel of a four-year ban due to a failed drugs test. If the 30-year-old faces the harshest punishment, his illustrious career might be abruptly over. Despite surged through a world-record £89 million transfer to Manchester United, a triumphant 2018 World Cup with France, his journey feels unfinished due to unsatisfactory tenure at Old Trafford and Juventus. </p>\n\n<h2>11:33 Man United`s Probability of a Top Four Finish Declines by a Steep 35%</h2>\n\n<p>Opta`s AI supercomputer reveals that Man United`s probability of securing a place within the top four this season has plunged by a staggering 35%. The team`s already rough start to the 2023-24 campaign has been exacerbated by defeat against heavyweights, Spurs and Arsenal. This disappointment comes in addition to the continuing saga revolving around Mason Greenwood, Jadon Sancho, and Antony has caused further disruptions in the United squad.  </p>\n\n<h2>10:36 Resolve Your Queries on Man United in Our Live Q&A</h2>\n\n<p>Throughout the day, Mail Sport`s experts will join us to share the latest team updates and answer all of your inquiries on Manchester United. The first to join us will be Mike Keegan, Mail Sport’s Sports News correspondent. He will be available from 12pm to answer your questions about Manchester United. Get your queries in the queue by commenting on the article or on our social media platforms. Click the link below and join in.</p>\n\n<h2>09:41 Update: Man United Set to Add American Goalkeeper Phallon Tullis-Joyce to Their Squad in a Record Deal</h2>\n\n<p>Following extensive negotiations between Man United and OL Reign, Phallon Tullis-Joyce`s home club, the goalkeeper is very close to joining United ahead of Thursday`s transfer deadline. The possible deal might replace the standing record fee for a goalkeeper, currently at £100,000.</p>\n\n<h2>09:30 Did Hannibal, Man United`s Youngster, Mimic Mohamed Salah?</h2>\n<p>Man United`s budding star, Hannibal Mejbri, seemingly imitated Mo Salah`s goal celebration after Tunisia defeated Egypt in a recent friendly. Tunisia’s victory was secured with a scoring of 3-1 in Cairo. The iconic Salah goal celebration was evident, acted out by Mejbri and Rafia after Tunisia’s win.</p>\n\n<h2>08:39 Man United`s Suspended Winger Antony Photographed Relaxed by a Pool in Sao Paulo</h2>\n<p>Sidelined due to assault accusations, Manchester United player Antony was recently seen spending leisurely time with friends by a pool, situated in a secure location close to Sao Paulo. Antony, keen to take a break after his suspension, had flown to Brazil after being excluded from the week`s International matches.</p>\n\n<h2>08:19 Unveiled: Man United`s New £60m Each Year Sponsorship with Snapdragon is a World Record Deal</h2>\n<p>After thorough negotiation, Manchester United confirms a £60million deal with American tech giant, Snapdragon, concluding its search for a new shirt sponsor. This whopping deal with the Qualcomm subsidiary surpasses the largest existing sponsorship agreement held by Real Madrid and Fly Emirates.</p>\n\n<h2>08:08 Harry Maguire: Southgate Criticises `Ridiculous` Accusations by `Our Own Pundits` following a Shocking Result with Scotland</h2>\n<p>Gareth Southgate comes out vehemently in defence of England’s defending pillar, Harry Maguire, decrying the criticism meted out to him as `absolutely laughable`. Maguire’s fellow England team members were also among those who voiced their support after an unfortunate own goal on Harry’s part that offered Scotland an unexpected lifeline in Tuesday night`s friendly at Hampden Park.</p>\n\n<p>Good Morning! Welcome to the Mail Sport`s live blog dedicated to all the Manchester United happenings. We will keep you updated with the latest news, rumors, and insights about the Red Devils throughout the day. Covering everything from Gareth Southgate`s spirited defence of Harry Maguire to the lingering issues surrounding Jadon Sancho and Antony, there`s a lot to delve into!</p>",
