      "Millions Beckon for Teen Prodigy Coco Gauff, as Tennis Victory and Big-Brand Partnerships Align",
    link: "https://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/tennis/article-12510341/Coco-Gauff-Open-champ-new-balance-bose-barilla-earnings-millions.html?ns_mchannel=rss&ns_campaign=1490&ito=1490",
    keywords: "null",
    creator: "null",
    description:
      "Not yet legally allowed to drink and just barely old enough to vote, US Open champion Coco Gauff has already earned more in her 19 years than most of us will in a lifetime.",
    content:
      "\n\n<p>While not yet old enough to legally consume alcohol and having just barely reached voting age, the young sensation that is Coco Gauff is already boasting earnings that would awe the average person. With her most recent winnings of $3 million from defeating Belarusian tennis player, Aryna Sabalenka, at the US Open championship, Gauff`s season earnings rose to a solid $5.5 million, enhancing her career prize money to an astonishing $11.1 million.</p> \n\n<h2>Sponsorship Spree</h2>\n\n<p>In spite of not possessing earlier highlight reel performances including a Grand Slam victory and a couple of recent single titles, the 19-year-old Florida native would still hold the title of a millionaire, thanks to a raft of endorsement contracts. Brands such as Barilla, UPS, Baker Tilly accounting have all formed partnerships with Gauff, whose knack for adorning her sponsors` paraphernalia was on display throughout the tournament.</p> \n\n<p>Whether she was donning a maroon New Balance outfit, sporting Bose headphones, or wielding a Head racket, Gauff ensured her patrons shared the limelight during her phenomenal journey of the past few weeks.</p> \n\n<h2>Financial Future Looks Promising</h2>\n\n<p>Though her endorsement profits for 2023 are yet officially unrevealed, a Forbes report from the previous year discloses that she raked in a cool $8 million from sponsorship deals in 2022 alone. Gauff is, in every sense of the word, a standout among her Gen Z sports equals.</p> \n\n<p>In keeping true to her generation, she took to social media before and after the match against Sabalenka, drawing strength from negative comments pre-match, and celebrating her victory with a TikTok post featuring the trophy afterwards.</p>\n\n<h2>Resilience on and off the Field</h2>\n\n<p>Gauff is notable for speaking her mind, without concern for the potential consequences from her sponsors. When climate change protesters interrupted her semifinal, she openly supported their cause and championed their right to make a stand. In the past, she`s drawn attention to issues such as gun violence in the US and women`s rights at various major events.</p> \n\n<p>While expressing gratitude for equal prize money for the women`s champion of the U.S. Open, she paid tribute to Billie Jean King. She frequently attributes her grounded nature to her family. Corey and Candi, her parents, along with the influence of her grandparents, has helped shape the phenomenal tennis player she is today.</p> \n\n<p>Gauff aspires `to keep improving,` candidly sharing that her performance against Sabalenka was nowhere near her best potential. Yet she won it, she suggests, purely on the merit of her athleticism. Gauff believes there is significant room for growth in terms of handling pace and ball-striking. For now, though, Gauff`s simple pleasure is to unwind by going to the beach, sleeping at home and getting away from the hotel room experience.</p> \n\n<p>NB: With her remarkable winnings tally, and huge promise of future sponsorships and endorsements, the tennis world eagerly watches to see how the teen sensation`s career unfolds.</p>",
