    description:
      "Mail Sport understands Tullis-Joyce is on her way to Manchester in the hope of completing a move, which could surpass the record fee for a goalkeeper, currently standing at £100,000.",
    content:
      "\n<p>In a crucial move just ahead of the upcoming deadline, Manchester United appears to be nearing the signing of American goalkeeper Phallon Tullis-Joyce. Negotiations with Tullis-Joyce`s existing club, OL Reign, have been keenly observed and it seems like both parties are reaching an agreeable conclusion soon. </p>\n\n<p>United`s potential contract with Tullis-Joyce is believed to exceed the current record fee for a goalkeeper coming in at £100,000. Reports indicate that Tullis-Joyce is en route to Manchester with hopes of sealing the deal before Thursday`s deadline, suggesting a positive outcome for the negotiations. </p>\n\n<h2>Retention of Lionsesses’ Star Mary Earps</h2>\n<p>Regardless of the impending sign-on of Tullis-Joyce, United appear determined to keep their current star, Mary Earps, in their roster. Despite being in the last official season with the club, Earps, who had expressed a desire to exit the club this summer, has had numerous bids rejected by Arsenal. United have assured the national goalkeeper that her standing with the team is solid, with expectations of maintaining the status quo until the deadline. </p>\n\n<p>The prospective acquisition of Tullis-Joyce is likely to stir up a healthy competition with Earps for the current season, while ensuring a proficient replacement for the near future as Earps has been reticent about signing a new contract. Consequently, her free transfer next summer is a possibility. </p>\n\n<h2>Sophie Baggaley’s Departure?</h2>\n<p>Should Tullis-Joyce’s move to United materialize, it is anticipated that Sophie Baggaley may be permitted to leave. Having been the second-in-command to  Earps last season, the 26-year-old`s future at United looks uncertain with the new signing. </p>\n\n<p>Man United’s latest developments in the team line-up promise a thrilling turn of events leading up to the approaching deadline. Stay tuned for more exhilarating insights with Mail Sport’s podcast, “It`s All Kicking Off!” available on various platforms such as MailOnline, Mail+, YouTube, Apple Music, and Spotify. </p>\n\n<p>Comment on this article and share your thoughts. Do you see Tullis-Joyce’s potential move to United as a refreshing change or a source of disruption? What are your thoughts on United’s stand on retaining Earps? Let`s start a discussion! </p>",
