    title:
      "Unveiled: The Striking Reason Kylian Mbappe Remained on The Bench in France`s Close Defeat to Germany",
    link: "https://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-12513005/The-reason-Kylian-Mbappe-bench-France-Germany.html?ns_mchannel=rss&ns_campaign=1490&ito=1490",
    keywords: "null",
    creator: "null",
    description:
      "Les Bleus suffered their first defeat in six games, losing 2-1 to their rivals on Tuesday evening - with Thomas Muller and Leroy Sane scoring for the hosts.",
    content:
      "\n\n<p>French football manager Didier Deschamps disclosed to the public why ace forward Kylian Mbappe was conspicuously absent from the field during France`s match against Germany.</p>\n\n<h2>Germany Triumphs Over France</h2>\n\n<p>In a 2-1 victory for Germany, Thomas Muller and Leroy Sane claimed the goals, sealing Les Bleus` first defeat in their past six encounters. This boost came only a few days after Germany showed the exit door to their manager, Hansi Flick — just nine months before the kick-off of Euro 2024 — due to successive poor performances.</p>\n\n<p>Rudi Voller, an ex-Germany forward, masterminded Germany`s victory over Deschamps` squad, bringing an end to their six-match winless streak against France.</p>\n\n<p>It was hard to overlook that Mbappe took a back seat in this match, failing to make an appearance despite France falling into a 2-0 deficit.</p>\n\n<h2>The Injury Puzzle</h2>\n\n<p>Mastermind Deschamps revealed post-match that Mbappe had suffered a knee injury in the training session preceding the match. This comes as good news to PSG fans, as Deschamps insisted the injury was not grave, and the sidelining was a measure taken out of caution.</p>\n\n<p>While speaking to L`Equipe: Deschamps stated, ”Kylian experienced a patellar tendon issue as a result of yesterday`s training — it`s not severe, but it is a concern that comes with risks. If he wasn`t fit enough to start, he couldn`t have been subbed in either.”</p>\n\n<h2>What`s Next?</h2>\n\n<p>France looks ahead to their next encounter in the Euro 2024 qualifiers when they visit the Netherlands in October. They`re leading the charge in Group B, holding a six-point lead over the Netherlands with just three matches left to play.</p>\n\n<p>Germany`s upcoming match will be on American soil, facing the United States on October 14, followed by a battle against Mexico four days after.</p>\n\n<p>Julian Nagelsmann seems to be an early favourite for stepping into the shoes of Flick to manage Germany.</p>\n\n<h2>Relief Amidst Challenges</h2>\n\n<p>Rudi Voller, Germany`s interim coach and sporting director, expressed relief at securing a win following their challenging period. After the France encounter, Voller said, ”The way we played, particularly in the first half, was a high-level performance. The victory brings relief for all of us and it feels great, especially after our recent losses.”</p>\n\n<p>Add your insights on this issue below, or engage in a lively discussion on our message boards. Remember to follow our house rules when posting your comments.</p>",
